🆕 :redsiren: Build Challenge:redsiren: 

We have a SPECIAL build challenge taking place from now until the end of February! In this challenge, we want to see what wonderous monuments (real or your creation), you can create in Minecraft Earth! These amazing builds will not only be ones we feature in social, but in a special GDC presentation as well! Let's get building!

:build_plate: Monument Challenge - February 18th to February 29th

📄 Guidelines:
:earth: Must be built in Minecraft Earth
:loading: This should be a brand new build and not be something that you've already built
:grass_block:  Build plate size will not matter & won't be a factor in judging
:mining: Feel free to ask for advice pertaining to your build in #monument-challenge  
:mob_of_me: All work must be done by one individual
:fast_parrot: Remember, this is for fun only
📌If it's a submission picture, please feel free to ask a moderator to pin it.
:sign: Winning submissions may be used in social media and in a GDC presentation :friends:

My submission for the #monument-challenge -

__*Monument for the Wildlife Lost in the Christmas Bushfires*__

This summer, Australia has suffered the worst bushfire season ever seen by man, with some fires continuously burning out of control from mid-December until February.

It's estimated that more than a billion (yes - that's right: a *billion*) animals lost their lives in the bushfires. Habitats have been destroyed, impacting countless species including many that are already endangered.

This monument is loosely based on the iconic photo from the fires I've included here.  I picture it as a peaceful place, popular with both animals and picnicking families. Kids (and wooly cows) love to climb to the top of the monument and enjoy the view.

The music (because I can't resist including music in all my builds) is *Waltzing Matlida,* considered by many to be the *"unofficial Australian national anthem."*

Source: https://sydney.edu.au/news-opinion/news/2020/01/08/australian-bushfires-more-than-one-billion-animals-impacted.html
